#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:258
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/body_fat_calculator.html:321
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/body_fat_calculator.html:422
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:197
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/healthy_weight_calculator.html:553
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/overweight_calculator.html:262
msgid "Obese"
msgstr "Otyły"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:295
msgid ""
"Body Mass Index (BMI) is a measurement of a person's leanness or corpulence "
"based on their height and weight, and is intended to quantify tissue mass. "
"It is widely used as a general indicator of whether a person has a healthy "
"body weight for their height."
msgstr ""
"Wskaźnik masy ciała (BMI) jest miarą szczupłości lub otyłości danej osoby na"
" podstawie jej wzrostu i masy ciała i ma na celu ilościowe określenie masy "
"tkanki. Jest powszechnie stosowany jako ogólny wskaźnik tego, czy dana osoba"
" ma prawidłową masę ciała w stosunku do swojego wzrostu."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:298
msgid "BMI = Weight (kg) ÷ Height (m)²"
msgstr "BMI = waga (kg) ÷ wzrost (m)²"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:301
msgid ""
"These ranges of BMI vary based on factors such as region and age, and are "
"sometimes further divided into subcategories such as severely underweight or"
" very severely obese. Being overweight or underweight can have significant "
"health effects."
msgstr ""
"Te zakresy BMI różnią się w zależności od czynników takich jak region i "
"wiek, a czasami są dalej dzielone na podkategorie, takie jak znaczna "
"niedowaga lub bardzo poważna otyłość. Nadwaga lub niedowaga może mieć "
"poważne skutki zdrowotne."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:310
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/overweight_calculator.html:323
msgid "Underweight: BMI &lt; 18.5"
msgstr "Niedowaga: BMI &lt; 18,5"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:312
msgid ""
"This range includes severe thinness (&lt;16), moderate thinness (16-17), and"
" mild thinness (17-18.5). You may need to gain weight. Consult with a "
"healthcare provider."
msgstr ""
"Zakres ten obejmuje dużą szczupłość (<16), umiarkowaną szczupłość (16-17) i "
"łagodną szczupłość (17-18,5). Być może będziesz musiał przybrać na wadze. "
"Skonsultuj się z pracownikiem służby zdrowia."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:316
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/overweight_calculator.html:329
msgid "Normal Weight: BMI 18.5-24.9"
msgstr "Normalna waga: BMI 18,5-24,9"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:318
msgid ""
"Congratulations! You are in a healthy weight range. Continue maintaining a "
"balanced diet and regular physical activity."
msgstr ""
"Gratulacje! Jesteś w zdrowym przedziale wagowym. Kontynuuj utrzymywanie "
"zbilansowanej diety i regularną aktywność fizyczną."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:322
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/overweight_calculator.html:335
msgid "Overweight: BMI 25-29.9"
msgstr "Nadwaga: BMI 25-29,9"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:324
msgid ""
"Consider a balanced diet and regular exercise. Small lifestyle changes can "
"help you reach a healthy weight."
msgstr ""
"Weź pod uwagę zbilansowaną dietę i regularne ćwiczenia. Małe zmiany w stylu "
"życia mogą pomóc w osiągnięciu zdrowej wagi."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:328
#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/overweight_calculator.html:341
msgid "Obese: BMI ≥ 30"
msgstr "Otyłość: BMI ≥ 30"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:330
msgid ""
"This includes Obese Class I (30-35), Class II (35-40), and Class III "
"(&gt;40). Consult with a healthcare provider for a weight management plan."
msgstr ""
"Obejmuje to otyłość klasy I (30-35), klasy II (35-40) i klasy III (>40). "
"Skonsultuj się z lekarzem, aby uzyskać plan kontroli wagi."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:341
msgid "Enter your age and gender"
msgstr "Podaj swój wiek i płeć"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:357
msgid ""
"Your calculated BMI number. This value is used to categorize your weight "
"status."
msgstr "Obliczona liczba BMI. Ta wartość służy do kategoryzacji stanu wagi."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:363
msgid ""
"The ratio of your measured BMI to the upper limit of normal BMI (25). Values"
" less than 0.74 indicate underweight, 0.74-1.0 is normal, greater than 1.0 "
"is overweight, and greater than 1.2 is obese."
msgstr ""
"Stosunek zmierzonego BMI do górnej granicy prawidłowego BMI (25). Wartości "
"mniejsze niż 0,74 wskazują na niedowagę, 0,74-1,0 na normę, powyżej 1,0 na "
"nadwagę, a powyżej 1,2 na otyłość."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:369
msgid ""
"Similar to BMI but uses height cubed instead of squared. More reliable for "
"very tall or short individuals."
msgstr ""
"Podobny do BMI, ale wykorzystuje wzrost w kostce zamiast w kwadracie. "
"Bardziej niezawodny dla osób bardzo wysokich lub niskich."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:375
msgid ""
"The weight range (BMI 18.5-24.9) considered healthy for your height. This "
"helps you understand your target weight range."
msgstr ""
"Zakres masy ciała (BMI 18,5-24,9) uznawany za zdrowy dla Twojego wzrostu. "
"Pomoże Ci to zrozumieć docelowy zakres masy ciała."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:388
msgid ""
"A circular gauge showing your BMI value visually. The color corresponds to "
"your category (blue for underweight, green for normal, yellow for "
"overweight, red for obese)."
msgstr ""
"Okrągły wskaźnik pokazujący wizualnie wartość BMI. Kolor odpowiada Twojej "
"kategorii (niebieski oznacza niedowagę, zielony oznacza normalną wagę, żółty"
" oznacza nadwagę, czerwony oznacza otyłość)."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:414
msgid "BMI Formula"
msgstr "Formuła BMI"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:416
msgid ""
"The equations used for calculating BMI in the International System of Units "
"(SI) and the US customary system (USC):"
msgstr ""
"Równania stosowane do obliczania BMI w Międzynarodowym Układzie Jednostek "
"(SI) i w zwyczajowym układzie amerykańskim (USC):"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:419
msgid "SI, Metric Units:"
msgstr "SI, jednostki metryczne:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:423
msgid "USC Units:"
msgstr "Jednostki USC:"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:430
msgid "BMI Table for Adults"
msgstr "Tabela BMI dla dorosłych"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:432
msgid ""
"This is the World Health Organization's (WHO) recommended body weight based "
"on BMI values for adults. It is used for both men and women, age 20 or "
"older."
msgstr ""
"Jest to zalecana przez Światową Organizację Zdrowia (WHO) masa ciała na "
"podstawie wartości BMI dla dorosłych. Jest stosowany zarówno u mężczyzn, jak"
" i kobiet, w wieku 20 lat i starszych."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:438
msgid "Classification"
msgstr "Klasyfikacja"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:439
msgid "BMI Range - kg/m²"
msgstr "Zakres BMI - kg/m²"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:443
msgid "Severe Thinness"
msgstr "Ciężka szczupłość"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:444
msgid "Moderate Thinness"
msgstr "Umiarkowana cienkość"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:445
msgid "Mild Thinness"
msgstr "Łagodna szczupłość"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:448
msgid "Obese Class I"
msgstr "Klasa otyłości I"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:449
msgid "Obese Class II"
msgstr "II klasa otyłości"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:450
msgid "Obese Class III"
msgstr "Klasa otyłości III"

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:476
msgid ""
"BMI is further influenced by factors such as age, sex, ethnicity, muscle "
"mass, body fat, and activity level."
msgstr ""
"Na BMI wpływają ponadto takie czynniki, jak wiek, płeć, pochodzenie "
"etniczne, masa mięśniowa, tkanka tłuszczowa i poziom aktywności."

#: Fitness_and_Health_Calculators/templates/fitness_and_health_calculators/bmi_calculator.html:482
msgid ""
"If you're concerned about your weight or BMI, please consult with qualified "
"healthcare professionals or registered dietitians."
